        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 10 at 9:59PM CDT by NWS Birmingham AL</headline>
        <description>At 958 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Jena, or 13 miles southeast of Gordo, moving east at 45 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Englewood, Ralph, Little Sandy, Maxwell, Taylorville, Fosters Boat
Landing, Hull, Hagler, Palmore Park, Stillman College, Duncanville,
McFarland Mall, Fosters, Pearson, Shelton State Community College,
Romulus, Tuscaloosa, Coaling, and Moundville.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 1100 PM CDT for
central and west central Alabama.</instruction>
